{"id": "113047", "title": "No children node listing when changing data source for a data set in data set editor page of the query tab.", "description": "When changing the data source for a data set in the data set editor page of the query tab, the children nodes are not listed as expected. The expected result is that when the data source is changed, the new data source's children should be listed.", "OB": "No children nodes are listed when changing the data source for a data set in the data set editor page of the query tab.", "EB": "After changing the data source, the children nodes of the new data source should be listed.", "SR": "To reproduce the issue: 
1. Create a new data set without a SQL statement. 
2. Open the data set editor and go to the data source page. 
3. Change the data source to a new one. 
Actual result: The new data source has no database/table/column information listed as children nodes. 

To workaround this issue, close the data set editor and reopen it."}
